text: I 100% don't get anime
Anything I've seen seems like something that would have a mediocre plot with lazy characters and cliched visuals if it were a movie, but it's a japaneese cartoon so it's art because weebs.
But I fully admit there may be something there I just don't get.

The Gundam universe is great, there's room for every taste, if you want a newer/more stylish one you can watch Gundam Seed or Gundam Wing both of them have a good story and are easier to watch. If you want to delve deep in the universe there's Mobile suit gundam 0079 , than Zeta Gundam(which is the best piece of anime I've ever watched), Double Zeta Gundam(Some say it's good. I couldn't watch it) then you go to an OVA Char Counterattacks and end with Gundam Unicorn(Which is also great), All of those are set in the same timeline so you get historic references from within the universe.
